39bbda178e7a902","position":"1784401803116457123-c49aafa1-575e-4100-8db3-abe0fd828659"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"e1dc6410-25d7-406a-b015-01c40c9fa16a","comments":[],"created_at":1784397311257720001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"Graduate src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py (867 LOC, over the 800 soft cap) off the module-size allowlist by extracting the cryptographic-identity & signed-attestation fold cluster into a NEW pure, stdlib-free leaf src/rebar/reducer/_processors_identity.py.\n\nMOVE (by name): _fold_author_attribution, _rederive_keyring_keys, process_key_event, _bootstrap_genesis_keyring, attestation_kind, process_signature. These reference only each other (a true leaf): process_key_event calls _rederive_keyring_keys; process_signature calls attestation_kind and _fold_author_attribution. _processors.py imports them back and re-exports them (# noqa: F401) so rebar.reducer._processors.<symbol> keeps resolving for the reducer dispatch table (_replay.py imports process_key_event + process_signature from ._processors) and for attestation_kind's importers (signing.py, _commands/verify_opcert.py, _opcert_signing.py, and tests). reducer/__init__.py needs no change.\n\nDEVIATION from the docs/architecture.md offenders row: that row names the seam _processors_keys.py with ONLY the 4-function keys cluster and explicitly flags it SUB-FLOOR (~84 LOC, below the 100-LOC leaf floor). This ticket WIDENS the seam to also move the attestation pair (attestation_kind + process_signature) so the new leaf clears the 100-LOC floor, and names it _processors_identity.py. _fold_author_attribution MUST travel with process_signature (its caller) into the leaf, else a back-edge cycle forms. The sub-floor _processors_keys.py row is stale/superseded and is DELETED by this ticket.\n\nThis is a pure/mechanical refactor: no signature or logic changes; E5 testing-plan is not-applicable — the existing reducer/attestation/signing test suites are the oracle.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] New leaf src/rebar/reducer/_processors_identity.py is in [100,800] LOC. Verified by: `lines=$(wc -l < src/rebar/reducer/_processors_identity.py) && [ \"$lines\" -ge 100 ] && [ \"$lines\" -le 800 ] && echo \"ok ($lines lines)\"`.\n- [ ] src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py is <=800 LOC (down from 867). Verified by: `lines=$(wc -l < src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py) && [ \"$lines\" -le 800 ] && echo \"ok ($lines lines)\"`.\n- [ ] The 6 named symbols live in the leaf and are re-exported (# noqa: F401) from _processors.py so back-compat holds. Verified by: `python -c \"from rebar.reducer._processors import process_key_event, process_signature, attestation_kind, _fold_author_attribution, _rederive_keyring_keys, _bootstrap_genesis_keyring; print('ok')\"`.\n- [ ] _processors.py removed from .github/module-size-allowlist.txt and .github/module-size-ceilings.txt. Verified by: `! grep -q '_processors.py' .github/module-size-allowlist.txt && ! grep -q 'reducer/_processors.py ' .github/module-size-ceilings.txt`.\n- [ ] The stale offenders-table row is deleted from docs/architecture.md. Verified by: `! grep -q _processors_keys docs/architecture.md`.\n- [ ] make lint passes (ruff check + ruff format --check). Verified by: `make lint`.\n- [ ] tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py passes (allowlist == over-cap set == ceilings keys). Verified by: `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py -q`.\n- [ ] The reducer/attestation/signing suites pass. Verified by: `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_attestations_reducer.py tests/unit/test_signing.py tests/unit/test_legacy_signature_mirror_drop.py -q` and `python -m pytest tests/unit -k 'reducer or attestation or signing' -q`.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/reducer/_processors_identity.py","reason":"new pure stdlib-free leaf holding the identity/keyring + attestation fold cluster"},{"path":"src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py","reason":"remove moved cluster; re-import + re-export the 6 symbols for back-compat"},{"path":".github/module-size-allowlist.txt","reason":"drop _processors.py row now that it is <=800 LOC"},{"path":".github/module-size-ceilings.txt","reason":"drop _processors.py ceiling row"},{"path":"docs/architecture.md","reason":"delete the stale sub-floor _processors_keys.py offenders-table remedy row"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","716f-b917-9fc8-41f5"]],"parent_id":"716f-b917-9fc8-41f5","parent_status_uuid":"c06ad1c0-312f-4aab-9a3c-7fdba07357bc","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":1,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["module-size"],"ticket_id":"10e3-709e-b1ff-4343","ticket_type":"story","title":"Split reducer/_processors.py — extract identity & attestation fold cluster into _processors_identity.py","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["da0b7d95-df5b-4d79-9d21-8184bcd08219","f1bec347-8ddd-441e-9dcd-cf7d631674f2","7ce7330e-d56c-456b-aea6-64ab4eea4303","adfb91e9-3adc-48af-aa0b-d45c13209fbd","c3fdb04f-65f9-4574-bb09-393ba5b6020b","c06ad1c0-312f-4aab-9a3c-7fdba07357bc","8379c969-3272-4206-956b-28fddb539641","c49aafa1-575e-4100-8db3-abe0fd828659"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784401803116457124,"uuid":"d81a954c-d2a9-4ce4-bbe9-c0421ba527df"}